<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11147a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11147a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11147a"> 147(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> troubadour / blue scarf / birch crown / bard</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> A ces deux signes, Tali&eacute;sinn reconnut dans son disciple le double don de l&apos;inspiration et la magie. Dans un chant solennel, Merlin se mit &agrave; pr&eacute;dire les futures victoires des Bretons et la grandeur d&apos;Arthur. Il re&ccedil;ut <mark>l&apos;&eacute;charpe bleue, la couronne de bouleau</mark>, et fut consacr&eacute; comme <mark>barde-devin</mark> dans la grotte d&apos;Ossian. <br><font color="green">[At these two signs Taliesinn recognized in his disciple the double gift of inspiration and magic. In a solemn song, Merlin began to predict the future victories of the Britons and the greatness of Arthur. He received the blue scarf, the birch crown, and was consecrated as a bard-diviner in Ossian&apos;s cave.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLG"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1921, 1892) 265</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
